What this gives you

This already lets you test questions like:
	•	Where should I open a coffee shop?
	•	Which neighborhood best fits my strengths?
	•	Which area looks crowded but still undervalued?
	•	Which places have momentum before everyone else notices?

⸻

Next upgrade: add time

Now the field starts breathing.

Add columns:

trend,momentum,volatility

Then update score:

time_factor = (1 + momentum) * trend / max(volatility, 0.5)
final_score = adjusted_score * narrative_multiplier * time_factor

Interpretation:
	•	momentum = is it accelerating?
	•	trend = is it moving generally upward?
	•	volatility = is it unstable or noisy?

That turns static ranking into trajectory ranking.

⸻

Next upgrade: add matchmaking

This is where your earlier game insight comes in.

Instead of “best location overall,” calculate:

fit_score = environment_score * operator_fit

Where operator fit can include:
	•	branding skill
	•	price sensitivity
	•	tolerance for competition
	•	ability to attract niche audiences
	•	speed of execution

So a hard market may be bad for most people but good for you.

That is the real edge:
not best in general,
best for this operator.

⸻

Next upgrade: spatial neighbors

A voxel should not be isolated.

Each cell should be influenced by adjacent cells:
	•	spillover traffic
	•	nearby prestige
	•	nearby decay
	•	competition overflow

Simple form:

blended_score = 0.7 * own_score + 0.3 * average(neighbor_scores)

Now you’re modeling fields, not just boxes.

